<emphasis bold="true" box="[712,865,2106,2135]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1921" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="201" pageNumber="480" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sylvanus">Akodon sylvanus Thomas, 1921</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3818814375" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">“Sunchal, 1200 m.” Restricted by |. P. Jayat and colleagues in 2007 to Sunchal (24°15’S, 64°26’W, 1454 m), Santa Barbara Department, Jujuy Province, Argentina.</materialsCitation>
This species is monotypic.
</paragraph>
