<subSubSection pageId="201" pageNumber="480" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6707536" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6707536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6707536/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="480" targetBox="[98,689,2109,2523]" targetPageId="201">
<paragraph blockId="201.[712,1304,2106,2529]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[712,888,2342,2371]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from a few localities in Sierra de Santa Barbara in SE Jujuy Province, NW 
<taxonomicName box="[914,1058,2421,2450]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Argentina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="201" pageNumber="480" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Argentina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="201" pageNumber="480" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="201.[712,1304,2106,2529]" lastBlockId="201.[98,1304,2535,3118]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[712,955,2460,2489]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 83-114 mm, tail 68-89 mm, ear 14-21 mm, hindfoot 22-27 mm; weight 16-35-5 g (mean 26 g). The Forest Grass Mouse is a moderately large species of 
<taxonomicName box="[246,343,2573,2606]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="201" pageNumber="480" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is olivaceous brown, finely streaked with black hair; venter and ears are similar to dorsum; eye-ring is either absent or weakly developed; white spotting on chin is barely developed; and tailis slightly bicolored, paler below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="201" pageNumber="480" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="201.[98,1304,2535,3118]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[100,210,2696,2725]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">Habitat.</emphasis>
Forest and high-elevation grasslands of the Yungas and Chacoan grasslands at elevations of 900-2400 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[100,600,2770,2803]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="201.[98,1304,2535,3118]" box="[100,600,2770,2803]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[100,361,2770,2803]" pageId="201" pageNumber="480">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
